This paper deals with the problem of subspace segmentation, which is a common task in computer vision and machine learning. The paper proposes a new method called Least Squares Regression (LSR) for subspace segmentation, which is based on data correlation and encourages a grouping effect. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves theoretical analysis of the objective function and data sampling, which suggests that it may also belong to the Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents experimental results on databases, which suggests that it may also belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
